  "summary": {
    "intent": "Implement the framework-agnostic `layout::collapsible` component (issue #275) in `ars-components` with full state machine, connect API, tests, snapshots, and audit coverage. A follow-up request also reorganized layout snapshot directories from a shared flat structure to per-component directories, matching the utility category pattern.",
    "outcome": "The Collapsible core was fully implemented and all quality gates passed (17 unit tests, 1 proptest, 7 spec-conformance, 9 snapshots, 89 mutants / 0 missed, 94.07% line coverage). Layout modules were refactored from flat `.rs` files to directory-backed `<component>/mod.rs` modules with co-located `snapshots/` directories. Spec files for core, Leptos, and Dioxus adapters were synced. The change was committed and a non-draft PR opened with `Closes #275`.",
    "learnings": {
      "repo": [
        "Layout components were historically flat `.rs` modules sharing a single `src/layout/snapshots/` directory; the correct pattern (matching utility) is directory-backed modules with `src/layout/<component>/snapshots/` per component.",
        "Snapshot filenames embed the full module path, so a frame test named `frame_root_aspect_ratio` was misrouted to the `aspect_ratio/` bucket during the automated snapshot move — file naming requires careful disambiguation when test names contain sibling module names.",
        "`cargo insta test --unreferenced=reject` is only meaningful when run against the full test surface; scoping it to a single component filter causes all other components' snapshots to appear unreferenced. Full-workspace sweep belongs in CI.",
        "The project uses GitHub Projects v2 with field IDs for status transitions; `gh project item-edit` with `--single-select-option-id` is required to move items between columns.",
        "Proptest coverage is a required gate and caught a real behavioral bug: changing collapsed-size props while in controlled mode accidentally cleared the controlled flag inside the `SyncProps` handler.",
        "`cargo mutants -p ars-components -f <file>` targets mutation to a single file; first run found 25 survivors, all in guard/sync/handler branches that lacked direct positive-path assertions.",
        "The `post-implementation-audit` skill is a mandatory step after named tests pass; it is expected to find spec drift and adapter-spec inconsistencies even when the core behavior is correct.",
        "Both adapter specs (Leptos, Dioxus) incorrectly documented that controlled `open` prop changes should dispatch `SetOpen`; the correct event is `SyncControlledOpen` — `SetOpen` is reserved for user-requested changes."
      ],
      "code": [
        {
          "path": "crates/ars-components/src/layout/collapsible/mod.rs",
          "finding": "SyncProps handler was accidentally dropping controlled mode when collapsed-size props changed; the fix separates the controlled-open field from the size-prop sync path."
        },
        {
          "path": "crates/ars-components/src/layout/mod.rs",
          "finding": "After converting flat layout modules to directory-backed modules, `mod.rs` pub-use declarations must be updated to match new paths; the layout mod was the only file needing explicit path changes."
        },
        {
          "path": "spec/leptos-components/layout/collapsible.md",
          "finding": "Adapter specs referenced `SetOpen` for controlled prop sync — corrected to `SyncControlledOpen` to match core machine contract."
        },
        {
          "path": "spec/dioxus-components/layout/collapsible.md",
          "finding": "Same controlled-sync event drift as the Leptos adapter spec; both were patched in the same audit pass."
        }
      ],
      "workflow": [
        "Running `cargo mutants` a third time after only moving a file (no logic changes) is unnecessary — a clean result from the previous run is sufficient evidence when the code body is identical.",
        "`cargo xci-fast` is reserved for the pre-commit/pre-push gate after explicit user approval, not during iterative development.",
        "TDD red-green discipline: adding failing test surface first, confirming compilation failure, then implementing, reduces the risk that tests never actually exercised a code path.",
        "When snapshot filenames contain multiple component names (e.g. `frame_root_aspect_ratio`), automated shell-based routing by substring match is fragile — verify the destination after a bulk move.",
